	</p>

	<p>
		Give a brief description of how we will breakdown this section.
	</p>


	<p>
		<me> \frac{d}{dx}[\ f \cdot g\ ] = \frac{d}{dx}[\ f\ ] \cdot g + f \cdot \frac{d}{dx}[\ g\ ]. </me>	
	</p>


	<p>
		As mentioned in the introduction, the integration factor method is a technique used to solve a differential equation of the form <xref ref="if-standard-eqn"/>. Its approach can be summarized through by two main tasks:
	</p>

